Thirdly, The ſeventh Vial being poured out, wherewith the Beaſt is diſpatcht and aboliſhed, there came a loud voice from the Throne, ſaying 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , It is done Chapter 16. verſe 17. So alſo he that ſate upon the Throne ſaith to John (beholding new Jeruſalem deſcending from Heaven) Chapter 21. verſe 5, 6. Behold I make all things
new;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , It is done, I am Alpha and Omega, the Beginning and the End: therefore new Jeruſalem the Bride of the Lamb, begins at the laſt end of the Vials 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , the Whore being already diſpatcht, and ſo it contemporizeth with the ſpace of time, which enſueth the deſtruction of the Beaſt.

